The paper deals with instance level visual recognition tasks, specifically object detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The algorithm presented in the paper involves processing context regions around ground-truth instances, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a region proposal network, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (cs.CL). Finally, the paper presents results on the COCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark for multimedia tasks (cs.MM).
